The square root of 2a minus 1

9
00:00:26.437 --> 00:00:28.500
Solution 1. Algebra

10
00:00:28.500 --> 00:00:38.812
The key is to notice that 2025 and 2026 are consecutive integers. let 2025 be n. so 2026 is n plus 1

11
00:00:38.812 --> 00:00:43.875
2025 equals n. 2026 equals n plus 1

12
00:00:43.875 --> 00:00:45.150
From the problem

13
00:00:45.150 --> 00:00:50.887
a equals n squared plus open parenthesis n plus 1 close parenthesis squared

14
00:00:50.887 --> 00:00:52.962
Compute 2a minus 1

15
00:00:52.962 --> 00:01:11.287
2a minus 1 equals 2 times open bracket n squared plus open parenthesis n plus 1 close parenthesis squared close bracket minus 1. which simplifies to 4n squared plus 4n plus 1. equal to open parenthesis 2n plus 1 close parenthesis squared

16
00:01:11.287 --> 00:01:12.262
Therefore

17
00:01:12.262 --> 00:01:22.175
The square root of 2a minus 1 equals the square root of open parenthesis 2n plus 1 close parenthesis squared. equal to 2n plus 1

18
00:01:22.175 --> 00:01:25.050
Substitute n equals 2025

19
00:01:25.050 --> 00:01:31.925
2n plus 1 equals 2 times 2025 plus 1. equal to 4051

20
00:01:31.925 --> 00:01:34.425
Answer. 4051

21
00:01:34.425 --> 00:01:37.762
Solution 2. Geometry or Dissection Method

22
00:01:37.762 --> 00:01:49.650
This method interprets the expression as area. in the figure below the parts 2026 squared. 2025 squared. and the center 1 are arranged into one large square

23
00:01:49.650 --> 00:01:57.737
